            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "1 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "Double-tap the power button to access\nthe system menu. From here you\ncan perform actions at any time like\nlocking the screen or shutting down\nthe system. Press the B or power\nbutton again to dismiss it."
            },
            { "x": 50, "y": 7, "image_path": "assets/arrow_up.png" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 1,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut1",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "2 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "The 'A' button (Green) is typically\nused to execute the selected\nelement.\n\nThe 'B' button (Red) is usually used\nto abort and return to the previous screen."
            },
            { "x": 50, "y": 175, "image_path": "assets/arrow_down.png" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 2,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut2",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "3 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "The direction buttons (D-Pad) allow\nyou to select on screen elements and\nnavigate the system. Their LED colors can\nbe controlled by payloads or from\nthe Settings > General > D-Pad LED\noptions menu."
            },
            { "x": 370, "y": 175, "image_path": "assets/arrow_down.png" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 3,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut3",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "4 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "The status bar displays system time, as\nwell as power state, volume,\nbrightness and vibration status.\n\nFrom Recon, the status bar will show\nGPS, database, PCAP and frequency."
            },
            { "x": 300, "y": 25, "image_path": "assets/arrow_up.png" },
            { "x": 251, "y": 5, "image_path": "assets/statusbar/vibrate.png" },
            { "x": 286, "y": 5, "image_path": "assets/statusbar/dashboard_brightness_7.png", "recolor_palette": "dark_green" },
            { "x": 317, "y": 5, "image_path": "assets/statusbar/volume_high.png" },
            { "x": 346, "y": 5, "image_path": "assets/statusbar/dashboard_battery_charge_75.png" },
            { "x": 400, "y": 7, "text": "1:37 PM", "text_color_palette": "dark_green", "text_size": "small" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 4,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut4",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "5 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "The system has three main modules:\nPineAP, Recon, and Payloads.\n\nIf you have experience with the WiFi\nPineapple or Hak5 gear, these should\nsound familiar. Let's break 'em down"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 5,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut5",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "6 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "PineAP is the core engine that allows you\nto execute WiFi operations. In addition\nto handshake acquisition, you may mimic\nopen and WPA networks while staying\nwithin the scope of engagement using\nAgent and Network filtering."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 6,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut6",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "7 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "Recon displays the wireless airspace\nat a glance with graphics, sounds\nand actionable data. Wardrive, save\npacket captures and interact with\nthe WiFi environment using payloads.\nSpeaking of payloads..."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 7,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut7",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "8 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "Payloads are executable scripts written\nin Bash and DuckyScript that let you\nwield the Linux power of the system.\n\nThere are three kinds of payloads:\nAlert, User and Recon."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 8,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut8",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "9 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "Alert payloads automatically execute\nwhen events occur in the airspace --\nsuch as detecting deauth floods, new\nhandshakes being acquired or agents\nconnecting to your WiFi Pineapple\nPager's rogue access point."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 9,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut9",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "10 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "User payloads can be executed anytime\nfrom the main Dashboard > Payloads\nmenu. You'll find a repository of\ncommunity developed payloads, as\nwell as documentation to write your\nown at https://hak5.org/pager\n"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 10,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut10",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "11 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "Recon payloads are a special type\nof payload which execute against a\ntarget observed from within Recon.\n\nUsing Recon payloads, you can easily\ninteract with the wireless environment."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 11,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut11",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "12 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "Settings is home to many features,\nlike 'Virtual Pager'. It lets you\ninteract with the system, access its\nterminal, download loot and more\nfrom a web browser via USB-C or WiFi\nvia the Management Access Point."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 12,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut11",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "13 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "The Management Access Point is your\nWiFi Pineapple Pager's private network.\nIt's intended for you, the\noperator, to access the system's SSH\nand Virtual Pager interfaces. Configure\nit from the Settings > Network."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 13,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut12",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "14 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "You can connect your system to the \nnetwork from the Network section of\nthe Settings menu. Scroll down to \nClient Mode Setup and follow the \nwizard. Then enable using the Client\nMode toggle switch anytime.\n"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 14,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut13",
          "selected_layers": [
            { "x": 400, "y": 40, "text": "15 of 16", "text_color_palette": "green", "text_size": "small" },
            {
              "x":128, "y":74, "text_color_palette": "black", "text_size": "small", "max_chars": 42, "wrap_text": true, "max_lines": 10,
              "text": "Once connected to the network via\nWiFi Client Mode, you're encouraged\nto check for system updates from\nthe Settings > Updates menu. Be sure\nto set your Timezone, date and time\nfor a reliable network connection."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "page_index": 15,
      "menu_items": [
        {
          "id": "tut14",
